consensus_analysis.root_cause: fabric.js Canvas Double Initialization via Multiple Loading Vectors
consensus_analysis.impact_assessment: User-blocking issue affecting core plugin functionality

priority_actions: Implement singleton pattern at fabric.js level

performance_assessment.memory_concerns: Multiple fabric.js instances cause memory leaks
timing_issues: Race conditions between vendor.bundle.js and fabric exposure

optimization_recommendations: Add singleton pattern to prevent memory duplication
bundle-performance-monitor.performance_impact: HIGH - Double initialization causes 2x memory usage

integration_assessment.plugin_conflicts: MEDIUM - Fabric.js global exposure conflicts possible
integration_assessment.maintainability: GOOD - Clear separation of concerns with proposed solution

solution_validation.singleton_approach: RECOMMENDED - Industry standard for this problem

implementation_phases: Phase 2: Update WordPress script loading order
Phase 3: Test and validate design save restoration
success_criteria: Zero 'fabric: Trying to initialize a canvas that has already been initialized' errors
Functional design save capability without errors
Stable canvas behavior across all user interactions
